WEBVTT

00:01.334 --> 00:03.632
l'll settle my bill for the month.
Let me see it.

00:03.703 --> 00:05.170
OK.

00:06.206 --> 00:08.640
- Ah. Here you go.
- All right.

00:09.175 --> 00:10.540
Whoa.

00:13.413 --> 00:16.177
And Jill said
l couldn't control myself. Whoa.

00:17.984 --> 00:19.884
Hey, guys.
Guess what?

00:19.953 --> 00:24.117
l have just been asked to star
in my very own video!

00:24.224 --> 00:26.658
<i>[chuckling] The Al Borland Workout?</i>

00:28.495 --> 00:31.589
<i>Abs of Flab.</i>

00:31.664 --> 00:35.225
That's something you want to see,
Al in a thong.

00:35.335 --> 00:37.860
''All right, girls, two, three...
Watch those carbs.

00:37.937 --> 00:40.667
Come on. Late night snacks,
that's a no-no.''

00:40.740 --> 00:43.004
lt's not an exercise video.

00:43.076 --> 00:46.375
<i>lt's called,
How to Stock Your Toolbox.</i>

00:46.913 --> 00:51.077
l will show beginners the tools
they need and how to use them.

00:51.651 --> 00:53.551
- Actually, you'd be good at that.
- Yeah.

00:53.620 --> 00:55.554
Hey, can l be in your video?

00:55.622 --> 00:59.558
<i>We never put you on Tool Time.
Why would Al put you in a video?</i>

00:59.626 --> 01:02.356
l got a lot of experience
in dinner theater.

01:05.565 --> 01:08.625
- You were an actor?
- No, a waiter.

01:11.438 --> 01:15.067
Well, l'm sorry, but casting
is entirely up to the producer.

01:15.141 --> 01:16.506
Yeah? Who's producing it?

01:16.576 --> 01:17.736
l am.

01:18.945 --> 01:21.038
But l would have to talk to my director.

01:21.114 --> 01:23.173
Who are you getting to direct it?

01:23.249 --> 01:25.809
Well, l would need someone experienced,
you know.

01:25.919 --> 01:28.479
Who knows tools, knows television

01:28.555 --> 01:30.853
and the Al Borland personality.

01:31.558 --> 01:34.322
Boy, that will be tough.
There is no Al Borland personality.

01:34.394 --> 01:38.956
You see? That's the humor that tells me
you're the man for the job.

01:40.333 --> 01:42.164
You want me to direct it?

01:42.235 --> 01:45.204
<i>Tim, you took Tool Time
from the ground up.</i>

01:45.305 --> 01:50.004
You gave it a visual style that has not
been seen on a cable television show.

01:50.844 --> 01:54.007
- Face it. You're a legend, Tim.
- Ah, yes.

01:56.182 --> 01:58.309
There's no money in this, is there?

02:00.420 --> 02:01.978
Not a nickel.

02:03.656 --> 02:06.022
And if you could bring a sack lunch...

02:08.961 --> 02:10.895
Hey! You could film it right here.

02:10.964 --> 02:12.795
lt'd be great publicity for the store.

02:12.866 --> 02:15.733
Well, as producer,
l would have to talk to my director.

02:21.975 --> 02:25.934
Well, as director,
l would have to OK it with my producer.

02:26.012 --> 02:27.570
Yeah!

